The paper deals with the network reliability problem in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also involves the analysis of the inhomogeneous random key graph, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper presents scaling conditions and numerical results, which are topics related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
